  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Around 90.000 patients have been hospitalised due to COVID-19 infection in France between&#xD;
      March 1st and June 15th; 19% of those requiring intensive care. Approximately 80% of these&#xD;
      patients have been discharged home by September 30th. Nonetheless, COVID-19 infection along&#xD;
      with intensive care consequences are very likely to impede those patients quality of life and&#xD;
      functional capacities.&#xD;
&#xD;
      This study aims to describe the quality of life outcomes and functional capacities of&#xD;
      COVID-19 survivors, at least 6 months after primary care hospital discharge.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
